    <div id = "about-site-container" class = "container">
      <h1>about the site</h1>
      <div>
        <p>The site is responsive, I used <strong>Bootstrap v4.6</strong>. For some parts I used native <strong>JavaScript</strong>, but I also used the <strong>jQuery</strong> library. Backend was written in <strong>Node.js</strong> using <strong>Express</strong>. The templating language is <strong>EJS</strong>. I used <strong>Git</strong> for version controlling. The site is deployed on <strong>Cyclic</strong> (obviously), a free alternative of <strong>Heroku</strong>. I use <strong>PostgreSQL</strong> and the <strong>no-SQL</strong> database <strong>MongoDB</strong>.</p>
        <p>Each site in the <strong>'things I can do'</strong> section represents a different skill. Neither of them was created by following a step-by-step tutorial. The next improvement will be integrating <strong>AWS S3</strong> to the file uploader and a sign in / out feature using <strong>Passport.js</strong> to restrict the news editor for authenticated users only.</p>
        <p>Currently I am focusing on <strong>React</strong>, also plan to learn the basics of <strong>Angular</strong> and later on, <strong>Python</strong>.</p>
        <p>Repository of the Node.js app: <a href = "https://github.com/stregie/about-me">https://github.com/stregie/about-me</a><br>
        Repository of the React app: <a href = "https://github.com/stregie/about-me-reactdev">https://github.com/stregie/about-me-reactdev</a></p>
